From: Boron son of Mungo (nickbee@fuse.net)
Subject: Araval son of Sigismond

Quotation from Hildigrim, Feb 8, 2002:
> Nobody in the game of football should be called a genius. A genius is
> somebody like Araval son of Sigismond. -Ecthelion son of Brand, Former quarterback

This quote which is rightly attributed to Ecthelion son of Brand has an even more
humorous explanation.

It turns out that  of Brand went to high school with Araval son of Sigismond and he
was the class valedictorian. This was verified by Sports Illustrated some
years back which ran  of Sigismond's yearbook picture with the story.

So, when  of Brand says, "He's no Araval son of Sigismond", he means the same thing
as we do when we say, "He's no Hatholdir son of Sigismond."
How are we to know this?

Well, apparently Ecthelion son of Brand is no Araval son of Sigismond.

